caption: I meet with friends this place from time to time! This is my favorite place to dine.  I go there frequently. The food is great, the workers are professional and the prices are affordable. I like going in this spot for a nice lunch.
I adore this venue very much. theres a great spirit. The meals are exeptionaly good. the service is efficient and the team is friendly. The cost is honest. I warmly recommend.
Get the red & black and tiramisu cakes!!

Last week was our first time we went to this fine restaurant. But It is obviously not the last time. We had a good time with the courteous service, with the fine  meal and booze and with the friendly charge. We will surely visit there in a short time.
Would certainly recommend visiting this place. Excellent ambience, delightful dishes, fantastic customer service. They never disappoint.
Nice spot for quality Cafe food. visited at eight, it was not full. the staff was very friendly and attentive. bring your appetite because portions are generous.
So so

This is a *genuine* French Cafe. The pastries are delicious, the quiches are delicious - I love that they have mini-quiches suitable for one or 2 people, the coffee drinks are delicious! My favorite place to go and so grateful they are so nearby!... GO! You'll love 💓 it! My favorite place for years!!!

From the moment  you step in this restaurant  team give you a good feeling. Very friendly hosts, it is a happy restaurant to hang out with buddies or with your date. Great  food, talented  chief cook and stuff, competitive  cost and nice  service. Warmly recommended.
Such an amazing place very peaceful and calm. Good music and atmosphere. Fast services with fairy prices. Good food and drinks. Friendly staff.
My top place for tasty Cafe food. Everyone at our table was quite pleased. Nothing but great experiences here. The bill was reasonable I would say.
Outstanding place for Cafe food. Great place to meet and catch up with friends. Prices are reasonable I would say. Food is like a place in Baltimore I loved.
Great 👍
A preferred spot for tasty Cafe food. food was super flavorful. the bill was average for the menu. i can see why they have so many good reviews.
Absolutely love this place. Have been buying Frasier and Spanish fruit cake from here for over 10 years. Best cakes I ever had to this day. Everyone I buy them for loves them.
cafe food at this place - very good. Loved this place from the first taste. Looking forward to going back again. This place has a good design.

This place is small, friendly, and everything there looks delicious. The coffee was great, but let me tell you-that bakery section-oh.my.gosh. Macarons all over the place, mini cakes, tiramisu...just amazing. I regret that I have nothing remotely like this here in my own hometown. If you are in Baltimore checking out the Mt Vernon neighborhood shoot down Charles and pay Cafe Poupon a visit. You will NOT be disappointed.

Our morning breakfast stop before leaving Baltimore. Both of us had a quiche (mini/personal size). Very flavorful - great ingredients and not too heavy. Coffee was good as were the pastries. Services is slow but personal. Other items on the menu looked great. Wonderful taste and just the right taste absolutely delicious and make you feel like what I have been missing
Cutest little French pastry cafe I stumbled upon.   Service was superb.  The Frazier was decadent.  Macaroons were very good too.
In all my years working in Baltimore I can’t believe I never knew about it until now. It’s a gem of a coffee shop that makes you feel like you’re in a Parisian cafe.
Brandy is the absolute best soul!! Her personality and baking are a cut above the rest!!!

A very cool place to be at. If you're in Baltimore, definitely check out out. The meat lovers quiche was a bit over salted but my boyfriend's quiche lorraine was perfect. I liked their coffee as well. The atmosphere is nice and welcoming.

I love this little gem! As a self-proclaimed Francophile, I sincerely appreciate the authentic feel of this cafe. My family has purchased cakes from the original Baltimore location on President Street for decades and the quality has been unwavering. Everything is intricately baked and decorated, but nothing beats the delicious taste. I've had every pastry offered over the years and the Royale is hands-down my absolute favorite. The coffee and lunch offerings are also fabulous. You can't go wrong visiting this place.
Fantastic shop.  Great coffee, friendly staff, and awesome food.  Will definitely go back.  Really clean shop.

If you don't have the cash to get to Paris, thank goodness there's Café Poupon. Everything here is buttery and elegant, which are pretty much my two must-have dining requirements. The cafe interior is cozy and inviting, with twinkling lights and whimsical rattan tables and chairs. The only thing sweeter than the elegant macaroons and aesthetically pleasing dessert slices are the staff. You can get a lot of different kinds of pastries, and real buttery quiche, and even homemade chicken pot pies! The salmon baguette I tried was so delightful.. and they serve illy coffee.. Oh, sweet cortado.. so go be happy and visit them. 💗
Great little French-style café in the heart of Baltimore City. Very nice décor and ambience. Food and coffee are top-notch too.
I really loved their food and service, awesome location very close to my apartment. The employees are always very kind. I highly recommend this place.
Best patisserie cafe in Baltimore city, hands down. A decent atmosphere for getting work done, although the tables address on the smaller side.
Great spot for specialty pastries.

This is my go-to place for lunch. I usually get the baguette, any of them is tasty and there are vegetarian options; toasted is best. The coffee is a dark French roast: smooth, a little smoky, tastes good with or without cream. I always enjoy the macarons. Service can be a little hit or miss, but nothing that keeps me away.

They close down food about 45-50 minutes before they close and won’t prepare anything else because they’ve put the food away early. Terrible customer service and insane to expect customers to be ok with not getting food service while they’re in fact still open.
Chocolate and nut lovers: Royale is the dessert to order
Fantastic pastries!
Very cute café, so glad I stopped in today. Staff was friendly, coffee delicious, and macarons are magnifique! Will definitely be back!
Greater coffee here, and lovely pastries from Patisserie Poupon. I like sitting by the window, or on nice days, in the outside seating that's a little hidden away from the street.
I love this place! Food's amazing and the coffee... It's just so good. The European style is perfect!
Good French baguette
Baguette sandwiches
Great coffee! (Illy!) Great pastries, savory and sweet! Going here for a bite will get me out of bed any day.

Nice Parisian cafe in downtown Baltimore. Charming atmosphere, incredibly delicious pastries, and good coffee. Yes, you can get Orangina here too! I definitely recommend the almond croissant. Lots of little seating areas, including some nice outdoor seating. Note, you're supposed to leave your dirty plate, cups, etc. on the table when you're done; they'll bus the table after you're gone (this wasn't obvious to me when I was there). Prices are a little on the high side. The only reason I didn't give it 5 stars is that I generally find the wait staff to be a little too much on the quiet/unfriendly side for me. Nonetheless, I really like this spot and come here at least once a month. Would recommend for a cup of coffee when travelling solo and for a small, intimate meeting alike (2-3 people). Beyond that the tables aren't big enough to accommodate.
Everything is delicious.
They were all very good but the gray one was my favorite
Amazing!
Better service could improve rating

Came here with my mom and a friend. Best approximation of a French pâtisserie I've come across in the US, I would have personally preferred more comfortable chairs or power points for laptops but this is not that sort of café (and there's nothing wrong with that).

Nice café with French style furniture. The food is ok but nothing special. Looks like a chain food than an artisan bakery. The risoto mushroom special was good but with a faded taste. The dessert is way too sweet killing anything else. The chocolate is not of good quality. The viennoiseries did not have a good look (undercooked and sugar glazing on top!
Nice place !
Delicious and beautiful cakes and desserts.  Much better than any grocery store baked goods and well worth the price.
Wish they were in Federal Hill

This is an adorable cafe with delicious baked goods. The cakes and tortes are second to none. The staff are incredibly helpful and tgis is a great place to get a treat for yourself or someone you care about. I do miss the lunch boxes that they used to sell.
Fantastic macarrones and cookies! Great coffee!
Always a go-to for great desserts.  Not a coffee drinker so I can't speak to that but they seem on point with it.
The eggplant quiche and drip coffee were good, but the Napoleon is horrible. I came here to try the Napoleon, almost impossible to eat. The only part that is decent is the cream.... could not eat it.
By far the best coffee and pastry in Bmore. The staff are very friendly and the vibe is amazing. Just wished they would have closed a bit later.
Nice coffee and light breakfast.

Love a local coffee shop with great pastries! Order the  tiramisu and cafe viennois and both were amazing! The tiramisu was amazing; everything was well balanced and it look beautiful. The whipped cream on top of cafe Vienna, you can see the the vanilla bean in it! Definitely will have to come back
Omg! I wish I had a picture.  I ate this stuff so fast. My first time here. Every thing was delicious!

The staff at the Lenore LOVES Cafe Poupon!  It is so convenient to walk to from all areas of downtown and even Mount Vernon, and it is well worth the trip.  The coffee is always spectacular, and nobody can compare to the pastries!  This place is a fantastic go-to if you need a sweet treat, but it's also a great spot to get lunch with a friend or colleague.  We always find ourselves bringing the yummy baked goodies back to the office, especially on a busy day when we need some extra "get up and go"!  Keep doing what you are doing, Cafe Poupon!  You rock!  Very Truly Yours, The Lenore Apartments
I ordered my husband’s birthday cake from here, and it was a hit!! Everyone inquired about the cake!

We have loved coming here since this place opened, but after our experience today we won’t be coming back. For my husband’s birthday today he specifically wanted to come here for a little bit to get a pastry and a coffee, and with our work schedules and traffic from another side of town we were happy we could make it in just before they closed. Their hours say they are open until 6 pm and we arrived at 5:40, after we stood in line we were told that their kitchen is closed, they only have a couple pastries left and their espresso machine has already been cleaned and they can no longer serve those beverages except for regular coffe. They put the pastries we got in a to go box, even though there was still time before they closed for us to be able to eat them there (5:52 to be specific) and at exactly 5:58 while we were sitting down (my husband was finishing the last bite of his pastry) we were told that they had to put up chairs because at 6 they are closing. When I asked about the espresso machine I was told that they start to clean it about 30 minutes before closing, so if you’re looking to get anything besides regular coffee my suggestion is try another place.  If your business is half closed 30 minutes before the time you state,  you should change your hours for slower weekdays, just like many other businesses do, and if your customers are clearly finishing up you don’t kick them out simply out of courtesy like pretty much any normal restaurant or cafe does.  Definitely very disappointed after this experience.
Simply delicious!!
Delish
Nice place to eat, great food. They need to train the staff to be at least more friendly and smiling.

The staff is friendly and the place is beautiful. More importantly, the pastries and the cakes are the best I've ever had. The coffee is delicious, the atmosphere is lovely, and we plan to have them cater our wedding.
Delicious coffee
Excellent coffee, great pastries, good which food. Nice place hidden mid block on Charles street.

Such a beautiful place to have afternoon tea with girlfriends, date nights with your partner, and even a mom daughter quality time kind of day. Amazing pastries, tasteful design, and friendly staff. Definitely recommended as a favorite and real “café”!!

Most of the food is good, but last time my dessert was absolutely terrible! It was the worst thing I have ever tasted. Today I went there and ordered some tea and a pastry. After I ordered, the tea came almost right away. Yet, I was waiting for my pastry since I prefer to eat my pastry with my tea. I was waiting and saw they were serving other customers and doing other things around the cafe. After about 10 minutes of waiting I walked up to the counter and asked them if they were going to be giving me the pastry I had ordered. They said it would be out shortly. Another 10 minutes went by and yet I still hadn’t recieved my pastry. At this point I was very upset. The pastry’s are pre-made and don’t have to do much to serve it. I was telling them that I was upset that they never gave me the pastry and they apologized many times and said they would refund me and give me the dessert free. In the end they gave me the dessert but at this point I was not going to eat it. This is the worst experience I have ever had at a cafe and it ruined my day completely. I do not recommend this cafe AT ALL. Terrible service and the food isn’t the best.
Ordered this cake which was pretty good. It was about $50. Occasionally I've gotten coffee and pastries from here also with no issues.

Wonderful pastries.
Nice food. Good atmosphere. Just wish they were willing to be open more often. Don't go around closing time because they are more interested in closing up than serving customers.
So so
Best bakery in entire city ❤

The only cafe open all day on New Year's Eve.  Croque monsieur was delicious. We came back here to work in the afternoon, and were given some extra macarons on the house! Such a nice spot and hope to return whenever we come back to Baltimore.
Great coffee and sandwiches.
Great desserts
Spam email from credit card use.  Avoid this place or use cash.

Café Poupon is a lovely French style café in downtown.  My wife and I had an amazing baguette.  My wife also ordered a coffee and when they brought it out they included a macaron at no charge which was a nice touch.  With excellent food and a charming ambience, Café Poupon is one of our favorite spots in Baltimore.
Nice ambience
Always love my visits to this amazing bakery.. The Opera torte, the Parisian, the Quiche and everything else soooooo very good.
We order some yummy pastries and desserts for the office and they were really good. Nicely price and as soon as you walked in the place smells amazing. It had a nice atmosphere and it was very clean.
Amazing food and drinks, really relaxing place

A moment of luxury in a chaotic day. The pastries here are made in-house and regularly brought out while you stare through the displays trying to decide what to indulge in. Might I suggest a perfectly flaky and buttery croissant or pain au chocolate (which has two bars of chocolate through it, as it should)? If you're in a sweeter mood the kouign amann is slightly over sugared but delightfully crunchy and caramelized all the way down, and the Parisian drinking chocolate makes for a spoil-yourself-break from their rich drip illy coffee. Whatever your order, just make sure you take a moment to stay and enjoy it. With an old world feel, fantastic ads from another era, and large shoppe windows to perch next to, this is a place to relax while the mad world continues outside without you.

(Translated by Google) I liked the place on the one hand the location nearby and the quiet and the attention and taste distinctive, although there are comments on the cleanliness, thank you to the owners of the cafe and the most beautiful greetings.  (Original) عجبني المكان من ناحية الموقع القريب والهدوء والاهتمام والطعم المميز ، وإن كانت هناك ملاحظات على النظافه ،  شكراً للقائمين على المقهى وأجمل تحيه .
Great coffee and quiche.

Got our wedding cake here and it was very affordable and quite delicious! We did a cake testing at the cafe and then picked up at the patisserie closer to home. The tasting was a very fun experience, and the free coffee (which was surprisingly good) was the cherry on top of it all.  We called plenty of local places for cake tasting, but Cafe Poupon was the only one who was kind and patient, and subsequently the only place we actually went in for a tasting. Everywhere else that's noteworthy in Baltimore for wedding cakes was seemingly annoyed by our call, and acted inconvenienced by even answering the phone. I'd suggest to any friends or family to give Cafe Poupon a shot, they are awesome and great with their customers.
Wonderful quiches, sandwiches, coffees and desserts with a nice patio on the side. Perfect!

Stopped by this sweet little French cafe on the recommendation of my boss. Love it! Their beverage selection is impressive (catering to both European and American tastes!) and the pastries are excellent. Looking forward to coming by here again to read and drink some Parisien sipping chocolate on a rainy day!

I've given this place so many opportunities but at last I've decided that it's just not worth the money. I've had several lunches here; the bakery items are nice but the menu items are either sparse for the cost that they ask for OR the menu items are not fresh, such as the salads.  For example, today I ordered the chicken mango salad and I had about four small pieces of grilled chicken in the middle of a bunch of lettuce with small bits of avocado and tomato.  Another time, there was a bug inside the lettuce - clearly not washed well. This is in addition to the food taking quite a bit of time for a cafe, and while I was waiting none of the staff updated me on how long my food would take or even apologize for the 15 minute wait time (no one else was waiting).  They should stick with just being a bakery and not offer meals.

This small French inspired cafe has an impressive array of pastries.  I tried the pear tart and my husband got the apricot tart. Both were good albeit quite a rich buttery pastry.  The coffee and chai latte are both good as well.  If it weren't so early when I visited I would have tried the drinking chocolate.  It's a European thing and is not hot chocolate.  Inquire about this if you visit.
Excellent service, great food and superb coffee!
The cake was amazing from the first bite! Sweetness is not too much and the staffs are so favorable and kind as well. I want to have em again over the short haul.
Excellent French Cafe.  Pattisserie Poupon Bread. Lovely salads.  Delicious coffee. Maybe the best mustard in Baltimore.  Go there happily.  Oh, fantastic pastries etc too
Excellent coffee and quiche. Fresh whole baguettes & croissants. Beautifully decorated pastry. A wee bit expensive for a light meal.
Had the tuna salad and napoleon dessert. Both fresh and delicious. Cafe is busy and management seemed present at all times.
Haven't gone yet.
Great service, excellent coffee, amazing pastries. We'll definitely be back the next time we're in town.
Hands down best chocolate chip cookies in Baltimore
Delicious pastries with amazing customer service. Great place to relax. Will definitely come back, if we make a trip back to Baltimore
I really like this place, a bit pricey, but the good is pretty good. The quiche is perfect!😍

This place is so cute! Sweet french cafe that gives a warm, inviting atmosphere. Friendly, helpful, knowledgeable staff too!!. Food is delicious! Everything tastes fresh and made with the best ingredients. I never leave reviews but I had to this time. Please do something nice for yourself and visit this place!!! 10/10 would reccommend
Real French pastry ! From someone who really likes pastry

I've been here a couple of times and it's definitely a pleasant place to grab a coffee or dessert and can be romantic if you're a Francophile.  The people working there were always very friendly and would offer explanations or recommendations when needed. There are quite a few dessert and food options, but almost all of them are small portions (by American standards) which I suppose is par for the course.  Despite the portion served, most everything I've tried has been flavorful and a delight to eat. My only criticism, and it's purely subjective, is there aren't many breakfast options that don't involve eggs and some kind of meat. To clarify, I mean this place appears to serve snack foods in that there aren't actual meals.  They have quiches, but they are small. Everything is all prepared and they don't actually serve to order. If you want a quiche or dessert they will heat it or just plate it, then serve it to you. It's probably a good business model but limited to the customers.  Also, the jug where you dispense water does so very slow into small glasses. If you're like me and drink a lot of water, then you'll end up going back to refill your glass several times and gets annoying.

My wife and I decided to get a cake from here for our rehearsal dinner because our cake was already included from our caterer on our wedding day. We got a sheet cake of the "Royale" and it was absolutely delicious! Everyone in the bridal party loved it and there was enough for people to take a slice to go. It was very moist and the crunchy hazelnut made it extra tasty. Highly recommend!

Cute, small French style cafe. The interior decor is very nice and the food is quite good. The sandwiches are very well done and the spreads are excellent. The coffee selection is very good. The regular drip coffee is well priced, tasty, and a generous portion.
Very dependable, excellent cafe food and coffee. Pastries from Patisserie Poupon, which are the best in the state.
OMG I don't know what I just ate, but I will certainly be returning. What my taste buds just experienced, deserves a treat as such, on the regular basis. Gym, we must do better!

A little pricey. But the food is worth it. I had a baguette, soy latte, and macaroon. It was my first time having a macaroon, and I have to say I was very pleased. I now understand why people love them so much. The baguette was very nice to have as a brunch portion. Just make sure not to put too much dijon mustard! Itll add a kick stronger than you will be ready for.
(Translated by Google) The pastries are very delicious and the people dont really nice !!  (Original) Les pâtisseries sont très délicieux et les gens dont vraiment agréable !!
Quaint, Charming, great Baguettes
Probably the best french bakery in Baltimore Never disappoints.

What a lovely place! I love Paris. I always thought there was too much hype around the city of lights and people seemed to revel in hating it and its famously rude residents. But when I visited it I fell hard for her. This cafe reminded me of the cafes in Paris. The place was well over staffed (I counted 6 people behind the counter) and I mean this as a compliment. The decor was detailed and obviously created with love. The menu was not deluged with endless options. The customers were dapper and friendly. The only thing not very French was the impeccable customer service and kindly fellow patrons. They even served humane portions of food. And it was very tasty and my mocha was delicious! Even the bathrooms did their best to mimic old world European feel but with all the spoiled American modern features! If you’re on Charles street and need some France in your life, head here.
Great pastries and food
The best pastries in Baltimore
Sent my mother to go in and get some pastries and coffee bc the traffic was thick and circled around the cashier was very helpful and made great selections all I can say is um um good 😋
Yummy food and cute atmosphere
Some of the best bread, pastries, and espresso in town. Espresso was remarkably smooth, and the tiramisu was the best I've had. Fully reccomend the whole grain sourdough baguette if they have it.
One of the nicest Cafè in Baltimore... Wide selection of sweets, croissants and other spécialités... Friendly staff and great atmosphere!!!

So far the best americano I had at Baltimore. The staff are really friendly
Delicious. Pleasant staff and great atmosphere.
Great place.

Love the smoked salmon, espresso and the Frasier! Truthfully all of the pastries are wonderful. I wish there was one in the county!

Great coffee and sandwiches! One of my favorite places for lunch downtown. Service can be a little below average at times.
Excellent for dessert with friends.
Very nice Madeleine and coffee. But pastry is not good enough.
Tasty espresso drinks and gourmet sandwiches. Price of sandwiches is somewhat high but quality is excellent.
The sandwiches are delicious and made from quality ingredients.  The coffee is good too.

Delicious food and coffee.
Quiche and croissants are amazing !

Ordered a King Cake the morning of Mardi Gras - cake was ready that day for pick up and was DELICIOUS. Not super traditional - was basically like a pecan filled croissant with frosting, but man was it good.  Pricey - but you get what you pay for
Great little place! Came here with my little ones and they loved it! They even gave me free madeleines 🤗
Simply Delicious Pastries

Really nice little cafe. The espresso is top-notch, and the pastries are quite delicious. You will definitely want to try a warmed up croissant if you come. The only downside is that the prices are pretty high, unless you get one of the morning combo deals.
Good but q little too pricey.

I don't spend much time in Baltimore, but I was in town for a couple of hours for an interview and passed this coffee shop on my way. They serve Illy espresso - delish! - and even gave me a free croissant (they were getting rid of the last one left, but the gesture was still appreciated).
loved it

Love this place. Great little French bakery in Mount Vernon. We live the ham and cheese croissants! Illy coffee, and excellent espresso drinks. Cookies, fruit trays and other pastries, plus savory options like quiches and sandwiches.
Beautiful pastries and excellent place to enjoy them!
Amazing croissants and best coffee in the city
Amazingly delicious and authentic French fare. Quick counter service.
Good coffee and pastry
Probably the best espresso in the city with a delicious bakery
Cute place with good soup. My sandwich was pre-made, so that was a little disappointing. My friend had the special, a risotto, and said it was pretty good.
This was the first time that I'd had authentic french baguettes and dijon mustard.  I certainly wasn't disappointed.
Great service, but the desert fell flat, as did the coffee. My tiramisu simply lacked moisture/freshness.  Really well decorated, and the staff seems to care.
I like this spot. The food is good, of late my favorite being their baguette sandwich and the coffee is very satisfying. Cheers to serving Illy!
Love the bread and pastries here! Delicious food, iced coffee could be better though.

Great espresso, nice staff, clean shop. My favorite morning stop. They have a $5 morning deal that's a life saver for my caffeine craving. Your choice of a latte or cappuccino with a croissant (chocolate, plain, or almond). Beats any $9 combo you would get at Starbucks. Don't forget to sign up for their rewards card. 10 visits get you a free coffee and other random freebies.
Great location.

Anytime you give me a free pastry with my espresso you earn a special place in my heart. To top it off we had the best pistachio eclair since we were in France!
Excellent espresso, eclair and croissant. This place reminds me of the little pastry shops in Marseilles.
Stumbled upon this cafe while in town for a conference. The cappuccino (well made!) and turkey brioche (with some spicy mustard) made for an excellent breakfast. Would definitely return.
Delicious french bakery with ever changing offerings. Take the advice of staff members, they know what is truly special!
Great pastries. Good coffee. Quiet.
Good coffee and macarons. Their sandwich bread is fairly dense and difficult to chew.  Could have been an off day.
One of my favorite places in downtown.  The food is superb. Too bad they are only open for lunch.
Good espresso, fresh pastries and baguettes, and great staff. Not nearly as much variety, but it's the closest thing to a Parisian boulangerie that Baltimore has.

Nothing really out of the ordinary "french-like" in there. My madeleines were made out of muffin mix in a madeleine shaped mold. My hot chocolate was tasteless, my espresso was not good (i suspect that staff is not trained well), chocolate cake was pretty bad to be honest (looks like they use sub-par chocolate and cacao, what a shame).  In the end, its a place with a french name that serves pretty boring/tasteless food at best.  I want to say, that it was maybe open in 1980 and did not evolve what so ever.
Lovely cafe, lovely food and lovely owner...I selected exactly what I wanted and came home to find a sweet surprise inside the box... Thank you! #happycustomer

I hosted a French wine tasting this week.  I had Cafe' Poupon cater my event.  Everything was delicious and the presentation superb.  I ordered Hors d' ouvres, mini quiche, charcuterie, fruit & cheese, mini French pastries & French baguettes.  Kate worked with me to insure I would have just the right assortment.  She was awesome!  The baguettes were still hot when I came to pick up my order.  The gentleman conducting my wine tasting is French and commented on the delicious cheeses!  Thanks to Kate & everyone at Cafe Poupon for making my event so successful!
Love it! Everything is homemade and delicious!
Delicious French pastries, food, and coffee. I've never been disappointed, and the staff is cheerful and helpful. Best croissants in the area!
